This paper deals with verifying the correctness of concurrent object implementations, which is a topic that falls under the programming languages (cs.PL), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also involves formal methods and automated theorem proving, which are relevant to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
